1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 20=

3
00:01:38,020 --> 00:01:39,660
(Dingqi Reading Platform)

4
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:40,510
Unfinished?

5
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:42,280
Unfinished...

6
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:44,000
So, how much was completed?

7
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:46,070
About a hundred thousand words.

8
00:01:46,333 --> 00:01:47,822
A hundred thousand words?

9
00:01:48,350 --> 00:01:50,510
If you stretch out the updates,

10
00:01:50,510 --> 00:01:52,000
the novel can last at most a month.

11
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:52,870
And then?

12
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:55,022
How are you going
to make your money back?

13
00:01:55,350 --> 00:01:56,350
Continue it.

14
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:03,510
A top author continuing
another top author's work.

15
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:05,150
That will draw a lot of readers.

16
00:02:05,790 --> 00:02:06,120
Look,

17
00:02:06,510 --> 00:02:08,630
it'll create controversy and buzz.

18
00:02:08,755 --> 00:02:11,555
Take Dream of the Red Chamber,
wasn't it continued by Gao E back then?

19
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:13,030
He Han won't agree.

20
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:15,360
He wants to write his own work.

21
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:18,280
No matter how famous
the Phantom Knight is,

22
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:20,710
He Han won't continue his work.

23
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:24,520
I can offer a lot of money.

24
00:02:27,700 --> 00:02:29,355
I'm afraid I won't be
able to persuade him.

25
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:31,800
If He Han refuses and Gu Yan agrees,

26
00:02:31,870 --> 00:02:33,310
all the attention will go to Gu Yan.

27
00:02:33,910 --> 00:02:36,310
Wasn't that your plan all along,
to give it to Gu Yan?

28
00:02:36,870 --> 00:02:38,840
You know
that He Han wouldn't agree, Fan.

29
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:40,660
You're using this
to win me over, aren't you?

30
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,190
Between He Han and Gu Yan,

31
00:02:42,190 --> 00:02:44,150
I have to secure at least one.

32
00:02:44,910 --> 00:02:45,520
Otherwise,

33
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:48,560
I'm afraid I won't
recover my investment.

34
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:50,800
Do you think Lin Zhanqiao

35
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:52,470
will let Gu Yan continue it?

36
00:02:58,266 --> 00:02:59,960
You don't need
to send it to me, Mr. Fan.

37
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:02,444
If it really was
written by Phantom Knight,

38
00:03:02,590 --> 00:03:04,150
I believe it must be good.

39
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:07,150
But Gu Yan really isn't
suitable to continue it.

40
00:03:07,910 --> 00:03:09,030
He's still a new author.

41
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:10,960
He should focus all his energy

42
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:12,710
on the work he already has right now.

43
00:03:14,630 --> 00:03:15,750
That's it for now. Bye.

44
00:03:40,460 --> 00:03:41,340
(Transfer to Ms. Dong)

45
00:03:41,340 --> 00:03:43,860
(Lin Zhanqiao:
You initiated a transfer.)

46
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,430
Miss Lin,

47
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:51,870
why are you transferring money to me?

48
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:54,933
About the food and expenses here,

49
00:03:54,977 --> 00:03:56,710
you need to take care of yourself first

50
00:03:56,710 --> 00:03:58,150
and then take good care of my mom.

51
00:03:58,360 --> 00:04:00,240
Our company doesn't allow us

52
00:04:00,470 --> 00:04:02,560
to privately accept tips from clients.

53
00:04:02,644 --> 00:04:04,240
Then, treat it as a shopping allowance.

54
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:06,710
Alright.

55
00:04:06,955 --> 00:04:08,840
My mom has fallen asleep,
so I'll leave first.

56
00:04:08,850 --> 00:04:10,555
I'll come by again tomorrow
when I have time.

57
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:12,190
Miss Lin, why don't you
wait a bit longer?

58
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:13,600
Your father will be here soon.

59
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,470
He said he's coming to see my mom?

60
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:17,950
He's bringing some TCM
for strengthening the body.

61
00:04:18,155 --> 00:04:20,733
He said he would leave it downstairs
and asked me to go get it.

62
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:21,800
I'll go get it.

63
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:23,120
I can talk to him for a bit.

64
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:23,950
Alright.

65
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:40,720
Dad.

66
00:04:42,622 --> 00:04:43,755
Here, give it to me.

67
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:48,950
Don't you have work?
You're coming twice a day.

68
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:50,560
Ms. Dong told you?

69
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:54,360
It's so late.
Your mom's still not asleep?

70
00:04:54,866 --> 00:04:56,170
She just fell asleep not long ago.

71
00:04:58,270 --> 00:04:58,750
See,

72
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:01,000
you do care about Mom.

73
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:02,070
Isn't that obvious?

74
00:05:02,444 --> 00:05:04,820
The three of us are family.
If anything happens to any of you,

75
00:05:04,830 --> 00:05:06,000
I should care.

76
00:05:06,830 --> 00:05:07,830
Then, how about

77
00:05:08,950 --> 00:05:10,680
we go have a meal with her tomorrow?

78
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:13,360
She usually goes out every day.

79
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:14,830
Now that she has to stay home,

80
00:05:15,044 --> 00:05:16,111
it must be quite boring.

81
00:05:17,190 --> 00:05:18,360
You go with her.

82
00:05:18,830 --> 00:05:19,630
I won't go.

83
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:22,510
Why are you like this?

84
00:05:23,266 --> 00:05:25,133
You'd rather carry such heavy medicine

85
00:05:25,140 --> 00:05:26,230
all the way here from so far

86
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:27,040
and stand downstairs,

87
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:29,155
but you won't go up to see her
or say a few words?

88
00:05:29,390 --> 00:05:32,000
We can't even get past
a few sentences when we meet.

89
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:33,360
Why bother?

90
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,160
Isn't this fine?

91
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:38,800
Ms. Dong said your mom
is in a good mood.

92
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:41,160
I've done what I should do,

93
00:05:41,430 --> 00:05:42,800
and I don't feel unwilling.

94
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:44,533
As long as she knows

95
00:05:44,577 --> 00:05:47,288
that if something happens,
I'll take care of her, that's enough.

96
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:49,870
Alright.

97
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:51,360
Wait here for a bit.

98
00:05:51,422 --> 00:05:52,910
I'll take the medicine
upstairs and then see you off.

99
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,260
No need. I'll go back on my own.

100
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:55,720
I'll get you a cab.

101
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:56,830
It's already so late.

102
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:59,070
I've timed it.
The subway is still running.

103
00:06:01,270 --> 00:06:02,160
Be careful.

104
00:07:35,420 --> 00:07:40,340
(Zhang Yousen: Your company owes
6,000,000 in back taxes, excluding late fees.)

105
00:07:45,060 --> 00:07:48,860
(Mr. He Han, we're waiting
for your update. Get well soon.)

106
00:07:58,680 --> 00:07:59,000
Here.

107
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:04,630
How is He Han?

108
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:07,720
Not very well.

109
00:08:10,577 --> 00:08:12,066
Aren't you going to see him?

110
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,630
I want to go see him,

111
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:20,311
but I don't know what to say.

112
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:26,310
I'm afraid I just wanted to say
a few words out of concern,

113
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,377
and it'll end up in another argument,

114
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:31,270
ending badly again.

115
00:08:35,670 --> 00:08:36,750
Right now,

116
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,750
it might be better

117
00:08:40,911 --> 00:08:42,577
to let him be alone for a while.

118
00:08:54,510 --> 00:08:55,080
He Wei

119
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,240
was ruthless.

120
00:09:05,270 --> 00:09:06,030
In the end,

121
00:09:09,670 --> 00:09:11,270
his dad pulled out the tube himself.

122
00:09:16,750 --> 00:09:17,790
That counts as suicide.

123
00:09:20,755 --> 00:09:21,960
Even at the very last moment,

124
00:09:24,790 --> 00:09:26,440
he still wanted to compete with He Han,

125
00:09:26,910 --> 00:09:28,480
to win or lose.

126
00:09:34,670 --> 00:09:36,080
Maybe he was like He Han,

127
00:09:38,870 --> 00:09:39,670
avoiding things.

128
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:42,270
He didn't know how to face

129
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:44,800
the reconciliation
that might come at the last moment.

130
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:47,750
Because if that happened,

131
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:49,960
he would regret

132
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:53,480
everything he had done to his son.

133
00:09:55,390 --> 00:09:56,550
So, he chose to run away.

134
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:01,960
Even though He Han
and I never get along,

135
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:04,030
sometimes,

136
00:10:04,030 --> 00:10:05,750
I understand some of his actions.

137
00:10:13,155 --> 00:10:14,030
Maybe it's because

138
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:15,550
we both had a terrible childhood.

139
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:08,940
(Mr. Fan: Reply when you wake up.
I need to talk to you.)

140
00:11:08,980 --> 00:11:11,300
(Fuchun Xiaolong Restaurant)

141
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:24,000
Mr. Fan, congratulations.

142
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:25,200
You've struck gold.

143
00:11:25,311 --> 00:11:27,270
You even managed
to dig up the Phantom Knight.

144
00:11:29,030 --> 00:11:29,870
How did you find out?

145
00:11:30,390 --> 00:11:31,870
If you didn't want people to know,

146
00:11:32,150 --> 00:11:33,480
no one would know.

147
00:11:33,790 --> 00:11:35,750
So, in the end,

148
00:11:36,030 --> 00:11:38,270
you allowed some of it to leak.

149
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:40,080
So, you must also know

150
00:11:40,577 --> 00:11:41,910
this is an unfinished manuscript.

151
00:11:41,977 --> 00:11:43,990
If it were complete,
it would've been published long ago.

152
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,933
It wouldn't have waited
for you to dig it up now.

153
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:46,960
So, who do you think

154
00:11:47,870 --> 00:11:50,270
can continue writing

155
00:11:50,466 --> 00:11:51,870
the Phantom Knight's work?

156
00:11:53,510 --> 00:11:55,150
In terms of popularity,

157
00:11:55,550 --> 00:11:56,670
He Han would be the closest.

158
00:11:57,390 --> 00:11:58,630
But he won't agree.

159
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:01,030
As for the others,
there's not much difference.

160
00:12:02,030 --> 00:12:02,670
Gu Yan.

161
00:12:03,390 --> 00:12:04,550
I have Hong Qigong on my side.

162
00:12:05,510 --> 00:12:07,750
Or maybe, Mr. Fan,
you've got your eye on some newcomer

163
00:12:07,910 --> 00:12:08,750
you want to promote?

164
00:12:08,750 --> 00:12:09,670
I only make money.

165
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:11,480
I don't promote people.

166
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:14,870
Then, you came to me for...

167
00:12:15,270 --> 00:12:15,910
Hong Qigong?

168
00:12:15,910 --> 00:12:17,790
She's older.

169
00:12:17,933 --> 00:12:19,620
When it comes to
building momentum later on,

170
00:12:19,644 --> 00:12:21,670
she won't have the same
advantage as younger authors.

171
00:12:21,750 --> 00:12:22,840
As for Gu Yan,

172
00:12:22,910 --> 00:12:24,960
shouldn't you be
talking directly to Lin Zhanqiao?

173
00:12:29,150 --> 00:12:30,630
If Lin Zhanqiao doesn't agree,

174
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:33,870
it won't be appropriate
for me to approach Gu Yan directly.

175
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:42,320
Don't worry.

176
00:12:43,030 --> 00:12:44,550
I won't let your help go unrewarded.

177
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:50,630
I help you convince Gu Yan

178
00:12:50,630 --> 00:12:52,510
to continue Phantom Knight's novel,

179
00:12:52,844 --> 00:12:54,150
and you'll help me convince him

180
00:12:54,270 --> 00:12:55,630
to move to Colorful Culture Media.

181
00:13:05,320 --> 00:13:06,630
Then, Lin Zhanqiao's company

182
00:13:06,630 --> 00:13:08,150
will be left with nothing.

183
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:10,120
There can't be two kings in one castle.

184
00:13:11,150 --> 00:13:13,510
If Gu Yan leaves,
He Han will be even more likely

185
00:13:13,510 --> 00:13:15,080
to return to Lin Zhanqiao's company.

186
00:13:15,266 --> 00:13:17,440
Then, your investment
in her company won't be a loss.

187
00:13:18,320 --> 00:13:20,510
If He Han doesn't go back,

188
00:13:20,750 --> 00:13:22,670
and you see value in Gu Yan's future,

189
00:13:22,850 --> 00:13:25,280
then investing in my company
works just the same.

190
00:13:25,790 --> 00:13:27,480
When it comes to cooperation,

191
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:29,200
I'm more flexible than Lin Zhanqiao.

192
00:13:38,900 --> 00:13:41,500
(Phantom Knight's unpublished work,
9 PM tonight, exclusive release!)

193
00:13:50,020 --> 00:13:51,340
(Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui)

194
00:13:55,860 --> 00:13:57,460
(Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui)

195
00:13:59,380 --> 00:14:02,020
(Phantom Knight's unpublished work,
9 PM tonight, exclusive release!)

196
00:14:02,020 --> 00:14:05,980
(Chenxing Culture Media
Keeping stories alive together.)

197
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:22,700
(Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui)

198
00:14:26,980 --> 00:14:28,460
(Dingqi Reading Platform real-time data.)

199
00:14:28,460 --> 00:14:30,460
(Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui)

200
00:14:34,380 --> 00:14:38,340
(Phantom Knight's final work to be
released exclusively tonight at 9 PM.)

201
00:14:45,630 --> 00:14:46,333
Ms. Lin.

202
00:14:48,755 --> 00:14:50,740
Gu Yan said the new update
is still being written.

203
00:14:50,750 --> 00:14:51,644
It'll be a bit late.

204
00:14:52,510 --> 00:14:53,240
What's the reason?

205
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:55,444
He didn't say.
Just said he can't write it.

206
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:03,750
Just a few days ago, he assured me

207
00:15:03,750 --> 00:15:05,066
he would write it properly.

208
00:15:05,550 --> 00:15:06,550
Was that just talk?

209
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:08,200
Should I follow up again

210
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:09,355
and ask what's going on?

211
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:10,390
No need.

212
00:15:12,870 --> 00:15:13,200
Then...

213
00:15:13,888 --> 00:15:15,960
I already told him
that if he misses another update,

214
00:15:15,960 --> 00:15:17,311
no one will help him again.

215
00:15:27,380 --> 00:15:29,620
(Drunk Old Friend-Outline)

216
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:40,355
(Cai Zhangzhu: Ms. Lin is angry.)

217
00:15:40,355 --> 00:15:44,900
(Please submit your draft
before we get off work.)

218
00:15:44,910 --> 00:15:45,933
(Gu Yan: Can you come see me?)

219
00:15:54,620 --> 00:15:57,740
(It seems closely related
to the clues they are looking for...)

220
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:12,320
How are you?

221
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:14,270
Why is it you?

222
00:16:14,466 --> 00:16:16,155
Zhangzhu has other work to handle.

223
00:16:16,222 --> 00:16:17,533
How much have you written?

224
00:16:18,440 --> 00:16:20,150
Or are you not planning to write at all?

225
00:16:20,550 --> 00:16:22,320
I wrote. I did write.

226
00:16:23,150 --> 00:16:23,510
But...

227
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:26,790
Look.

228
00:16:27,510 --> 00:16:29,150
These are five different drafts.

229
00:16:29,750 --> 00:16:30,360
Five drafts?

230
00:16:31,030 --> 00:16:32,080
You wrote five versions?

231
00:16:33,670 --> 00:16:35,240
Why did you suddenly take this approach?

232
00:16:36,510 --> 00:16:38,200
Because I don't trust my own judgment.

233
00:16:39,044 --> 00:16:41,200
I asked Zhangzhu to come,
so she could help me see

234
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,240
which version is better.

235
00:16:42,355 --> 00:16:43,550
I just hope there's one version

236
00:16:43,550 --> 00:16:44,480
you'll think is good.

237
00:16:44,733 --> 00:16:46,220
But I keep feeling something is off.

238
00:16:48,244 --> 00:16:49,630
No one writes online fiction like you,

239
00:16:49,630 --> 00:16:50,960
making five drafts at once.

240
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:53,840
Take a look first.

241
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:11,688
The six million in
back taxes and late fees

242
00:17:13,070 --> 00:17:13,960
is not a small amount.

243
00:17:22,711 --> 00:17:24,200
If Lawyer Bei doesn't acknowledge it,

244
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:26,510
you should be prepared
to take legal action.

245
00:17:27,110 --> 00:17:27,920
I already asked him.

246
00:17:28,110 --> 00:17:29,200
He said he's out of town

247
00:17:29,377 --> 00:17:31,711
and told me not to worry,
and to wait until he gets back.

248
00:17:34,030 --> 00:17:35,590
From a business standpoint,

249
00:17:35,920 --> 00:17:36,720
he's a lawyer.

250
00:17:37,790 --> 00:17:39,000
He won't leave behind anything

251
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,350
you can use against him.

252
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:44,000
I suggest

253
00:17:44,422 --> 00:17:46,755
approaching this from
your personal relationship.

254
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:48,200
Find a way to prove

255
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:50,200
he lured you into
a personal relationship

256
00:17:51,310 --> 00:17:52,440
and used your trust

257
00:17:53,066 --> 00:17:55,022
to get you to set up a company for him.

258
00:18:00,640 --> 00:18:01,350
How do I prove it?

259
00:18:03,644 --> 00:18:05,240
From when you first met him until now,

260
00:18:05,644 --> 00:18:06,830
your complete chat records

261
00:18:08,270 --> 00:18:09,510
and everything you can remember

262
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:11,510
that shows his intentions weren't pure,

263
00:18:11,955 --> 00:18:13,155
all of those accounts.

264
00:18:14,110 --> 00:18:15,270
If possible,

265
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:16,777
audio recordings would be best.

266
00:18:18,030 --> 00:18:18,880
That won't work.

267
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:20,920
Any other way?

268
00:18:22,590 --> 00:18:23,790
Also, for something like this,

269
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:26,555
I think what he fears most
is his wife finding out.

270
00:18:26,911 --> 00:18:28,000
That's even less possible.

271
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:31,920
At this point, you
shouldn't still be expecting

272
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:33,955
him to be someone
you can trust or rely on.

273
00:18:39,550 --> 00:18:40,240
Even if he is,

274
00:18:41,590 --> 00:18:43,350
you should prepare for the worst.

275
00:18:54,920 --> 00:18:56,590
You know where he handles cases, right?

276
00:18:58,155 --> 00:18:58,960
I'll go find him.

277
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:02,240
Whether he's sincere

278
00:19:02,830 --> 00:19:03,590
or a liar,

279
00:19:05,444 --> 00:19:07,490
I'll confront him in person
and get a clear answer.

280
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:11,350
So, which one is better?

281
00:19:14,933 --> 00:19:16,377
Let's go with the first draft.

282
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:18,240
There isn't much time left.

283
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:20,480
Why the first version?

284
00:19:26,510 --> 00:19:28,400
Because none of them
are particularly strong.

285
00:19:29,133 --> 00:19:31,022
Let's just submit
something for today first.

286
00:19:31,133 --> 00:19:32,000
For the later parts,

287
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,670
I'll go through them
with you step by step.

288
00:19:33,680 --> 00:19:34,160
Also,

289
00:19:34,466 --> 00:19:35,440
don't overthink it.

290
00:19:37,590 --> 00:19:38,720
I'm not overthinking.

291
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:41,750
I just want to write something good,

292
00:19:42,440 --> 00:19:44,160
something that you, the editors,

293
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:45,680
and Dingqi Platform think is good,

294
00:19:46,480 --> 00:19:47,955
not just something to get by.

295
00:19:53,270 --> 00:19:54,310
Every author

296
00:19:54,320 --> 00:19:56,022
has to write thousands
of words every day,

297
00:19:56,030 --> 00:19:57,510
updating for years on end.

298
00:19:57,977 --> 00:20:00,266
There will always be times
when your state isn't good.

299
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:02,790
I'm afraid that even
when I feel I'm in a good state,

300
00:20:03,310 --> 00:20:05,070
to you, it might only be passable.

301
00:20:07,750 --> 00:20:08,955
You should head back first.

302
00:20:09,088 --> 00:20:10,880
There are still a few hours
before the deadline.

303
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:12,111
I'll think it over a bit more.

304
00:20:12,311 --> 00:20:13,444
How about this?

305
00:20:13,666 --> 00:20:15,610
I'll go through the key plot points
for the next

306
00:20:15,790 --> 00:20:17,200
few chapters with you right now.

307
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,720
I've already caused you
too much trouble.

308
00:20:19,955 --> 00:20:21,266
I'll handle it myself.

309
00:20:21,750 --> 00:20:22,680
How is this trouble?

310
00:20:24,577 --> 00:20:26,955
When have I ever said
you were causing me trouble?

311
00:20:28,140 --> 00:20:30,340
(Drunk Old Friend: Hidden Depths)

312
00:20:40,022 --> 00:20:42,333
Are these
the previous chapters He Han wrote?

313
00:20:43,070 --> 00:20:44,030
How do you have these?

314
00:20:45,022 --> 00:20:46,180
Did Zhangzhu give them to you?

315
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:46,590
No.

316
00:20:47,790 --> 00:20:49,880
I did ask her,
but she wouldn't give them to me.

317
00:20:50,244 --> 00:20:51,933
I got them from someone else.

318
00:20:53,244 --> 00:20:54,822
Since this chapter isn't being used,

319
00:20:55,266 --> 00:20:57,000
there's no need to look at it anymore.

320
00:20:57,240 --> 00:20:58,711
You're afraid I'll be discouraged?

321
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:00,880
Just like Zhangzhu said,

322
00:21:01,310 --> 00:21:02,590
he writes well, better than I do.

323
00:21:03,030 --> 00:21:03,720
That's why

324
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:05,300
you've been pushing yourself this hard,

325
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:06,755
writing five drafts in one go?

326
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:08,790
Since so many
people have seen his draft,

327
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:11,000
I have to prove to them, to you,

328
00:21:11,070 --> 00:21:12,644
that I can write better than he does.

329
00:21:13,022 --> 00:21:14,888
Otherwise, how embarrassing
would that be?

330
00:21:15,177 --> 00:21:16,400
People would laugh at you,

331
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:18,977
saying you gave up
something big for something small.

332
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:22,920
You're thinking too much.

333
00:21:23,750 --> 00:21:24,510
He Han

334
00:21:24,510 --> 00:21:25,830
stopped updating because of his

335
00:21:25,830 --> 00:21:26,680
own personal reasons.

336
00:21:27,270 --> 00:21:28,200
If I were you,

337
00:21:28,270 --> 00:21:29,510
I would take this opportunity

338
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:31,244
to rally readers and increase updates.

339
00:21:31,310 --> 00:21:33,022
That's the most effective approach.

340
00:21:34,733 --> 00:21:36,888
Send me this version.
I'll format it when I get back.

341
00:21:38,070 --> 00:21:39,720
I want to see an extra chapter from you

342
00:21:40,030 --> 00:21:41,350
before the end of today.

343
00:21:43,880 --> 00:21:44,400
As for this,

344
00:21:44,466 --> 00:21:45,733
you don't need to look at it.

345
00:22:11,550 --> 00:22:12,590
Sorry, I'm rushing a draft.

346
00:22:12,590 --> 00:22:13,844
I don't have time to chat.

347
00:22:13,888 --> 00:22:15,030
How late do you need to work?

348
00:22:15,030 --> 00:22:15,480
7 PM.

349
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:18,510
Alright, I'll wait outside.

350
00:22:18,577 --> 00:22:19,880
Let me know when you're done.

351
00:22:28,844 --> 00:22:30,270
I've sent you Phantom Knight's

352
00:22:30,270 --> 00:22:31,510
Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui.

353
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:32,720
Take a look first.

354
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:35,240
If you think it's good,

355
00:22:36,030 --> 00:22:38,160
you can seriously consider
letting He Han continue it.

356
00:22:38,160 --> 00:22:40,780
("Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui"
by Phantom Knight)

357
00:22:42,260 --> 00:22:43,460
(Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui)

358
00:22:44,060 --> 00:22:45,340
(Prologue: A Fleeting Dream)

359
00:22:56,790 --> 00:22:57,400
Fan.

360
00:22:57,750 --> 00:22:58,640
Have you read it?

361
00:22:59,777 --> 00:23:00,688
What do you think?

362
00:23:01,030 --> 00:23:01,880
Is it good?

363
00:23:04,510 --> 00:23:05,270
Let me tell you,

364
00:23:05,830 --> 00:23:06,640
we've decided

365
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:09,022
to release
Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui

366
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:11,440
two hours earlier.

367
00:23:12,240 --> 00:23:12,720
Fan,

368
00:23:12,920 --> 00:23:15,830
are you sure this
was written by Phantom Knight?

369
00:23:16,270 --> 00:23:17,000
Or rather,

370
00:23:17,240 --> 00:23:18,350
are you sure it's his work,

371
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:19,880
written four years ago?

372
00:23:20,680 --> 00:23:23,240
Of course. I paid a lot for this.

373
00:23:23,510 --> 00:23:25,830
Don't worry. I'm more cautious than you.

374
00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:10,790
Dingqi is releasing

375
00:24:10,960 --> 00:24:12,920
Phantom Knight's unfinished novel,

376
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:14,333
Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui.

377
00:24:16,750 --> 00:24:17,880
Phantom Knight?

378
00:24:20,244 --> 00:24:21,444
How is that possible?

379
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:24,400
Fan already sent me the manuscript.

380
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:26,680
Do you know this novel?

381
00:24:29,480 --> 00:24:30,030
No.

382
00:24:31,310 --> 00:24:32,720
You're sure you've never seen it?

383
00:24:32,960 --> 00:24:33,350
No.

384
00:24:36,070 --> 00:24:37,160
Then, I'll send it to you.

385
00:24:37,200 --> 00:24:37,720
No need.

386
00:24:43,790 --> 00:24:44,590
These past few days,

387
00:24:44,590 --> 00:24:47,510
I wasn't planning to bother you

388
00:24:48,350 --> 00:24:49,070
with work matters.

389
00:24:49,070 --> 00:24:50,310
But with things like this,

390
00:24:51,240 --> 00:24:53,440
there might be some issues.

391
00:24:54,640 --> 00:24:55,400
What issues?

392
00:24:56,640 --> 00:24:58,920
Some parts of
Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui

393
00:24:58,920 --> 00:25:00,911
are similar to Shattered Six States.

394
00:25:01,640 --> 00:25:02,488
That's impossible.

395
00:25:03,755 --> 00:25:06,355
He hadn't even released his novel.
Where was I supposed to copy it from?

396
00:25:06,590 --> 00:25:08,240
I'm not saying you copied it,

397
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:11,480
but these days,
people talk about "plot overlap."

398
00:25:11,830 --> 00:25:13,680
I'm worried someone might say that,

399
00:25:13,750 --> 00:25:15,400
and it could affect your reputation.

400
00:25:15,880 --> 00:25:16,880
How would that affect me?

401
00:25:17,640 --> 00:25:18,790
Great minds think alike.

402
00:25:19,350 --> 00:25:20,680
Yes, that's true,

403
00:25:20,680 --> 00:25:23,310
but we should think ahead
about how to respond...

404
00:25:23,310 --> 00:25:24,590
They haven't even said anything.

405
00:25:24,590 --> 00:25:26,030
Why should we prove ourselves first?

406
00:25:55,310 --> 00:25:56,590
Luo, a basket of buns, please.

407
00:25:56,644 --> 00:25:57,733
Coming right up.

408
00:26:00,822 --> 00:26:01,910
You haven't eaten this late?

409
00:26:01,920 --> 00:26:02,200
Here.

410
00:26:03,911 --> 00:26:04,888
Finished writing?

411
00:26:05,511 --> 00:26:06,790
What exactly do you want from me?

412
00:26:10,577 --> 00:26:12,160
I want to give you an opportunity,

413
00:26:12,333 --> 00:26:13,480
one that might let you

414
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:14,960
surpass He Han in popularity.

415
00:26:15,590 --> 00:26:16,400
Are you interested?

416
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:18,310
What opportunity?

417
00:26:18,822 --> 00:26:19,977
Take a look at this first.

418
00:26:22,860 --> 00:26:26,020
(Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui,
Phantom Knight)

419
00:26:30,300 --> 00:26:33,420
(Prologue: A Fleeting Dream)

420
00:27:04,133 --> 00:27:05,844
(Lawyer Bei is in Yichun, Jiangxi.)

421
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:18,830
The number you dialed
is currently unavailable.

422
00:27:19,240 --> 00:27:20,640
Please try again later.

423
00:27:27,700 --> 00:27:30,220
(Lawyer Bei: In court. Talk later.)

424
00:27:31,866 --> 00:27:32,822
Where are you?

425
00:27:33,066 --> 00:27:34,270
Have you reached Lawyer Bei?

426
00:27:34,577 --> 00:27:36,022
I'm almost in Yichun.

427
00:27:53,960 --> 00:27:54,440
How are you?

428
00:27:54,822 --> 00:27:55,960
What did Lawyer Bei say?

429
00:27:57,440 --> 00:27:58,750
He's in court and hasn't replied.

430
00:28:00,480 --> 00:28:01,000
In court?

431
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:02,110
That's possible,

432
00:28:02,577 --> 00:28:04,377
but it shouldn't take
more than half a day.

433
00:28:06,750 --> 00:28:08,110
I know he's avoiding me.

434
00:28:11,960 --> 00:28:14,680
If there's a court nearby, it should be
the No. 1 Intermediate Court.

435
00:28:15,311 --> 00:28:17,711
There are hotels nearby.
You can try finding him there.

436
00:28:18,955 --> 00:28:20,750
I don't want to act
like a desperate woman,

437
00:28:20,790 --> 00:28:22,270
blocking him for an explanation.

438
00:28:22,350 --> 00:28:23,070
Six million

439
00:28:23,880 --> 00:28:25,044
is not a small amount.

440
00:28:28,555 --> 00:28:29,488
It's my mom.

441
00:28:33,200 --> 00:28:33,830
Hello, Mom.

442
00:28:34,844 --> 00:28:36,844
I'm on a business trip.
I'll be back tomorrow.

443
00:28:39,488 --> 00:28:40,790
Which charging cable is broken?

444
00:28:40,790 --> 00:28:41,977
I'll buy you a new one.

445
00:28:43,888 --> 00:28:45,222
You're already at my place?

446
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:49,640
There's a cable on my desk.

447
00:28:49,640 --> 00:28:50,977
You can use that for now.

448
00:28:52,270 --> 00:28:52,640
Alright.

449
00:28:53,070 --> 00:28:54,110
I'll talk to you later.

450
00:28:54,310 --> 00:28:54,720
Bye.

451
00:29:12,720 --> 00:29:13,444
What's wrong?

452
00:29:13,511 --> 00:29:15,600
Your mom calls,
and you look like the sky is falling.

453
00:29:17,790 --> 00:29:18,590
No.

454
00:29:18,933 --> 00:29:21,070
I was wondering if my mom
showing up out of nowhere

455
00:29:22,480 --> 00:29:24,000
would make me slip up.

456
00:29:51,590 --> 00:29:52,400
But probably not.

457
00:29:52,822 --> 00:29:54,133
I checked everything.

458
00:29:59,960 --> 00:30:00,830
What are you writing?

459
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:03,960
I'm writing what you
should say to Lawyer Bei

460
00:30:04,377 --> 00:30:06,177
and the questions you need to ask him.

461
00:30:06,533 --> 00:30:07,888
Have you booked a hotel?

462
00:30:08,590 --> 00:30:09,030
No.

463
00:30:10,244 --> 00:30:12,266
I plan to head back
right after I see him.

464
00:30:18,030 --> 00:30:19,510
Xinggui Hotel is nearby.

465
00:30:19,911 --> 00:30:21,200
I'll wait for you there,

466
00:30:21,288 --> 00:30:22,310
in case you need backup.

467
00:30:25,240 --> 00:30:25,920
Lawyer Bei

468
00:30:26,288 --> 00:30:28,066
doesn't know I followed you to Yichun.

469
00:30:28,480 --> 00:30:29,790
So, if you need anything,

470
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:31,510
call me, and I'll be there right away.

471
00:30:32,288 --> 00:30:33,830
How could you possibly be his match?

472
00:30:34,733 --> 00:30:35,755
Not necessarily.

473
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:40,640
He asked me to handle

474
00:30:40,640 --> 00:30:42,070
the company under your name.

475
00:30:42,600 --> 00:30:44,066
He had already planned it out.

476
00:30:44,800 --> 00:30:46,200
He knows that on one hand,

477
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:47,590
I need to keep my job

478
00:30:48,310 --> 00:30:49,790
and the promotion he promised me,

479
00:30:50,933 --> 00:30:52,244
and on the other hand,

480
00:30:52,311 --> 00:30:53,400
I have to protect you.

481
00:30:53,533 --> 00:30:54,640
If it were someone else,

482
00:30:54,844 --> 00:30:56,480
they might not consider your feelings.

483
00:30:57,310 --> 00:30:57,720
So,

484
00:30:58,590 --> 00:31:00,240
before this matter is settled smoothly,

485
00:31:00,830 --> 00:31:01,400
he needs me.

486
00:31:01,960 --> 00:31:03,960
After it's resolved,
if everything stays quiet,

487
00:31:05,200 --> 00:31:06,070
I keep my mouth shut,

488
00:31:06,111 --> 00:31:07,377
and he has no reason

489
00:31:07,880 --> 00:31:08,790
to replace me.

490
00:31:09,750 --> 00:31:10,720
If he comes after you,

491
00:31:12,310 --> 00:31:13,350
I'm not unprepared.

492
00:31:19,400 --> 00:31:20,550
What have you prepared?

493
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:23,750
He's a top lawyer.

494
00:31:24,030 --> 00:31:24,680
He has a family

495
00:31:25,350 --> 00:31:27,400
and far more to worry about than I do.

496
00:31:27,866 --> 00:31:28,480
But I don't.

497
00:31:29,200 --> 00:31:30,600
I only need to look after you.

498
00:31:31,533 --> 00:31:32,480
That's why I said,

499
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:34,920
he's not necessarily my match.

500
00:31:43,444 --> 00:31:45,177
I don't need you to do all this for me.

501
00:31:47,590 --> 00:31:49,720
Just give me information and advice.

502
00:31:51,030 --> 00:31:52,680
Doing this won't benefit your future,

503
00:31:55,350 --> 00:31:56,510
and it won't move me.

504
00:31:58,550 --> 00:32:00,880
If you've never been loved
or protected without hesitation,

505
00:32:01,070 --> 00:32:02,550
how do you know you won't be moved?

506
00:32:03,110 --> 00:32:04,310
Someone like Lawyer Bei

507
00:32:04,830 --> 00:32:06,550
would never do this for you.

508
00:32:07,377 --> 00:32:08,640
Even if you're not moved,

509
00:32:08,711 --> 00:32:10,400
you should at least experience it.

510
00:32:11,200 --> 00:32:12,160
Maybe after you do,

511
00:32:12,720 --> 00:32:13,550
you won't admire

512
00:32:13,550 --> 00:32:14,600
someone like him anymore.

513
00:32:14,620 --> 00:32:15,740
I've grown up all these years,

514
00:32:15,755 --> 00:32:18,111
and you think you're
the first man to risk everything for me?

515
00:32:20,111 --> 00:32:22,590
If I've never experienced it,
is it because I don't like it?

516
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:33,311
No matter what you think,

517
00:32:34,066 --> 00:32:35,222
this is what I want to do,

518
00:32:36,030 --> 00:32:37,590
and what I can do for you.

519
00:32:37,680 --> 00:32:38,550
And after that?

520
00:32:39,666 --> 00:32:42,160
If your life, finances, and work
all fall apart, what will you do?

521
00:32:42,160 --> 00:32:43,030
That's my problem.

522
00:32:43,800 --> 00:32:45,110
If you're worried about that,

523
00:32:45,110 --> 00:32:46,377
you're underestimating me.

524
00:32:57,960 --> 00:32:59,288
He said to meet at 9 PM.

525
00:33:12,030 --> 00:33:12,720
Coming.

526
00:33:18,160 --> 00:33:18,830
Who is it?

527
00:33:19,030 --> 00:33:19,480
Delivery.

528
00:33:21,488 --> 00:33:22,880
Hello, delivery for Miss Zhou.

529
00:33:23,070 --> 00:33:23,830
Okay, thank you.

530
00:33:23,933 --> 00:33:25,844
No need to close the door.
I'll handle it.

531
00:33:26,240 --> 00:33:26,640
Thanks.

532
00:33:35,955 --> 00:33:36,933
What's wrong?

533
00:34:34,377 --> 00:34:35,533
Why didn't you pick up?

534
00:34:35,600 --> 00:34:37,333
A battle has to be
fought one step at a time.

535
00:34:37,360 --> 00:34:38,955
Deal with the immediate problem first.

536
00:34:48,480 --> 00:34:50,880
At the end,
there's a Q&A and discussion.

537
00:34:52,488 --> 00:34:54,710
Ten thousand words a day.
The pace is picking up.

538
00:34:54,840 --> 00:34:56,044
The new draft quality is good.

539
00:34:56,177 --> 00:34:57,711
Why are you in such a good state?

540
00:34:58,960 --> 00:35:00,070
Because I want to try

541
00:35:00,590 --> 00:35:02,030
starting another project.

542
00:35:04,760 --> 00:35:06,030
This is your first novel.

543
00:35:06,320 --> 00:35:07,630
I hope you give it your all.

544
00:35:08,088 --> 00:35:10,850
They're looking for an author to
continue Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui.

545
00:35:10,866 --> 00:35:11,733
Have you heard?

546
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:13,866
That's just a publicity stunt
by Dingqi Platform,

547
00:35:13,911 --> 00:35:15,070
meant to grab attention.

548
00:35:15,070 --> 00:35:16,550
But Phantom Knight is my idol.

549
00:35:16,670 --> 00:35:18,400
Reading your idol's work

550
00:35:18,710 --> 00:35:20,190
and working hard to become an author

551
00:35:20,710 --> 00:35:22,670
readers love, just like him,
will do, too, right?

552
00:35:23,320 --> 00:35:25,920
If I could continue
Phantom Knight's novel,

553
00:35:26,440 --> 00:35:27,280
my name

554
00:35:27,280 --> 00:35:28,920
would be written alongside his.

555
00:35:28,960 --> 00:35:30,400
That would be an honor for me.

556
00:35:30,533 --> 00:35:33,030
Continuing someone else's novel
is not an easy job.

557
00:35:33,710 --> 00:35:34,670
If you do it well,

558
00:35:35,070 --> 00:35:35,760
people will say

559
00:35:35,760 --> 00:35:38,044
it's because Phantom Knight
set it up well at the start.

560
00:35:38,150 --> 00:35:39,230
But if you don't do well,

561
00:35:39,311 --> 00:35:41,360
they will say you aren't good enough,
ruining a great work with a bad ending.

562
00:35:41,360 --> 00:35:42,400
I'm a new author.

563
00:35:42,577 --> 00:35:44,488
Even if I don't write as
well as Phantom Knight,

564
00:35:44,600 --> 00:35:46,111
it's nothing to be ashamed of.

565
00:35:46,800 --> 00:35:47,590
And I believe

566
00:35:48,044 --> 00:35:50,030
I can produce something
above my current level.

567
00:35:51,311 --> 00:35:52,590
Besides, I have you, don't I?

568
00:35:52,840 --> 00:35:53,280
Right?

569
00:35:53,622 --> 00:35:54,955
I'm not getting involved.

570
00:35:55,150 --> 00:35:55,630
Why not?

571
00:35:56,480 --> 00:35:58,190
I can barely keep up with my own work.

572
00:35:58,320 --> 00:35:58,800
Why would I

573
00:35:58,800 --> 00:36:00,550
continue someone else's novel?

574
00:36:00,800 --> 00:36:02,710
But he's not just anyone.
He's Phantom Knight.

575
00:36:02,710 --> 00:36:03,700
Do you even know who he is?

576
00:36:03,710 --> 00:36:04,590
Even I don't know.

577
00:36:04,644 --> 00:36:07,311
I even doubt whether what's
been released was really written by him.

578
00:36:07,360 --> 00:36:09,960
Based on what's been published,
it does seem like his writing.

579
00:36:10,070 --> 00:36:11,360
In the current market,

580
00:36:11,360 --> 00:36:13,000
only He Han writes in a similar style.

581
00:36:13,155 --> 00:36:15,650
So Dingqi Platform will surely
approach He Han to continue it.

582
00:36:15,960 --> 00:36:16,960
If He Han agrees,

583
00:36:17,230 --> 00:36:18,590
I'll lose this opportunity.

584
00:36:18,590 --> 00:36:19,400
He won't agree.

585
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:22,590
His own novel is currently on hiatus.

586
00:36:22,688 --> 00:36:23,510
While he's on hiatus,

587
00:36:23,510 --> 00:36:25,390
this is your best chance
to secure the top spot.

588
00:36:25,630 --> 00:36:27,480
You should focus fully on your own work.

589
00:36:28,070 --> 00:36:29,230
So you still don't agree?

590
00:36:30,200 --> 00:36:31,088
I don't agree.

591
00:36:33,440 --> 00:36:34,070
Lin Zhanqiao,

592
00:36:35,670 --> 00:36:37,070
when it comes to my own writing,

593
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:39,800
may I get a say?

594
00:36:40,880 --> 00:36:42,110
Can't you consider

595
00:36:42,110 --> 00:36:43,440
my interests and preferences?

596
00:36:44,280 --> 00:36:45,480
At least listen to me,

597
00:36:45,480 --> 00:36:47,311
talk through
Parting with Yan Dan with me,

598
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:50,270
and then discuss objectively
whether continuing it is even possible,

599
00:36:50,280 --> 00:36:52,280
before rejecting me.
That would make me feel better...

600
00:36:52,280 --> 00:36:52,840
But the issue

601
00:36:52,840 --> 00:36:54,550
is that this project
doesn't suit you at all.

602
00:36:54,550 --> 00:36:56,688
We're not even
at the stage of discussing content.

603
00:36:57,030 --> 00:36:57,710
And I won't

604
00:36:57,710 --> 00:36:58,920
bend the truth

605
00:36:59,070 --> 00:37:00,590
just to make you feel better right now.

606
00:37:00,590 --> 00:37:01,760
You're not listening to me.

607
00:37:03,070 --> 00:37:04,550
You just want me to listen to you.

608
00:37:05,190 --> 00:37:07,920
You assume you've already made it
into the top authors' circle,

609
00:37:07,920 --> 00:37:09,830
and now you're making
demands here and there.

610
00:37:09,840 --> 00:37:11,630
But you've only been
in this field for a year,

611
00:37:11,630 --> 00:37:13,110
and you're looking around like this.

612
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:15,320
Sooner or later, you'll be replaced.

613
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:16,110
Replaced by who?

614
00:37:17,466 --> 00:37:19,480
So, you mean you have
so many new authors on hand

615
00:37:19,711 --> 00:37:20,840
that you can just pick one

616
00:37:20,888 --> 00:37:22,840
and train them to replace me?

617
00:37:23,800 --> 00:37:26,150
I want to keep working
with you, project after project.

618
00:37:27,360 --> 00:37:28,360
Can you stop saying

619
00:37:28,590 --> 00:37:30,155
you'll replace me?

620
00:37:31,066 --> 00:37:33,111
When things didn't work out
between you and He Han,

621
00:37:33,320 --> 00:37:34,480
you wanted me to replace him.

622
00:37:34,533 --> 00:37:36,488
Now that things aren't
working between you and me,

623
00:37:36,511 --> 00:37:37,711
you want to replace me.

624
00:37:37,755 --> 00:37:38,920
What are you trying to say?

625
00:37:38,920 --> 00:37:40,320
I never said that!

626
00:37:40,320 --> 00:37:41,800
I never said anyone would replace you.

627
00:37:41,840 --> 00:37:43,150
But that's what you're thinking.

628
00:37:43,150 --> 00:37:44,577
That's what you're preparing.

629
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:46,230
That's your trump card.

630
00:37:58,960 --> 00:38:00,360
It's not easy to cultivate a writer.

631
00:38:03,480 --> 00:38:04,440
They're hard to come by.

632
00:38:06,480 --> 00:38:07,550
Developing new writers

633
00:38:08,920 --> 00:38:10,590
is a necessary reserve for the company,

634
00:38:10,960 --> 00:38:12,550
not to replace you.

635
00:38:13,550 --> 00:38:15,577
You're overthinking this.

636
00:38:16,670 --> 00:38:18,510
If you want to develop a new project,

637
00:38:18,510 --> 00:38:19,230
that's fine.

638
00:38:19,440 --> 00:38:20,800
But after you've completed

639
00:38:20,920 --> 00:38:22,880
two-thirds of your current work,

640
00:38:23,222 --> 00:38:24,933
we will discuss it then, alright?

641
00:38:28,555 --> 00:38:30,422
Continuing
Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui

642
00:38:30,440 --> 00:38:31,710
might be a chance to stand out

643
00:38:31,710 --> 00:38:33,320
for other new authors.

644
00:38:33,630 --> 00:38:34,840
But for you,

645
00:38:35,550 --> 00:38:37,230
it's really not worth the effort.

646
00:38:40,666 --> 00:38:43,000
If there's anything else
you want to discuss,

647
00:38:44,510 --> 00:38:45,480
I can sit down now

648
00:38:45,755 --> 00:38:47,177
and talk it through with you.

649
00:39:13,920 --> 00:39:14,480
He Han.

650
00:39:19,070 --> 00:39:19,630
He Han.

651
00:39:46,740 --> 00:39:48,755
(No. 29-32, Building 24,
Husong Building Materials Market,)

652
00:39:48,755 --> 00:39:50,340
(Lane 6700 Songbei Road,
Songjiang District)

653
00:40:08,311 --> 00:40:10,911
When will the person
delivering the switch covers arrive?

654
00:40:10,955 --> 00:40:12,044
They'll be here shortly.

655
00:40:19,311 --> 00:40:20,377
What are you looking for?

656
00:40:21,222 --> 00:40:22,022
Light bulbs.

657
00:40:22,488 --> 00:40:24,133
Did you bring any?
What kind do you need?

658
00:40:24,960 --> 00:40:25,710
3.5 watts.

659
00:40:25,880 --> 00:40:26,320
Screw base.

660
00:40:26,670 --> 00:40:27,311
Small or large?

661
00:40:27,630 --> 00:40:27,960
Large.

662
00:40:29,000 --> 00:40:29,440
How many?

663
00:40:31,030 --> 00:40:31,440
Two.

664
00:40:32,110 --> 00:40:33,150
Nineteen yuan for two.

665
00:40:33,177 --> 00:40:34,280
Scan to pay with WeChat.

666
00:40:34,290 --> 00:40:35,310
I'll get the bulbs for you.

667
00:40:53,900 --> 00:40:55,511
(Recommended to use WeChat Pay)

668
00:40:56,260 --> 00:40:59,740
(Payment to individual: Xu Fenglian)

669
00:41:14,440 --> 00:41:15,320
Ms. Xu, right?

670
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:16,360
Yes.

671
00:41:19,360 --> 00:41:21,280
Didn't you live
near Damuqiao Road before?

672
00:41:21,590 --> 00:41:22,000
No.

673
00:41:22,150 --> 00:41:23,822
I've lived in Songjiang my whole life,

674
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:25,030
never left.

675
00:41:30,444 --> 00:41:31,630
A friend of mine's mother

676
00:41:31,630 --> 00:41:32,800
has the same name as you.

677
00:41:34,466 --> 00:41:35,155
That's strange.

678
00:41:35,400 --> 00:41:37,500
Yesterday, someone else
came asking questions, too,

679
00:41:37,777 --> 00:41:39,933
saying there's someone
with the same name as me.

680
00:41:43,880 --> 00:41:44,630
Someone else came?

681
00:41:45,150 --> 00:41:45,590
Yes.

682
00:41:46,280 --> 00:41:47,710
A woman, around thirty,

683
00:41:47,960 --> 00:41:49,550
tall and thin, with short hair.

684
00:41:53,800 --> 00:41:55,333
What are you looking for her for?

685
00:41:56,800 --> 00:41:57,360
Nothing.

686
00:42:01,666 --> 00:42:02,488
Here are your bulbs.

687
00:42:02,760 --> 00:42:03,110
Alright.

688
00:42:03,480 --> 00:42:03,920
Thank you.

689
00:42:19,340 --> 00:42:22,740
(Year 1992)

690
00:42:38,620 --> 00:42:46,420
(Shanghai Xintuo Fasteners Wholesale)

691
00:43:01,380 --> 00:43:04,180
(Thanks.)

692
00:43:05,921 --> 00:43:07,041
(I've been thinking.)

693
00:43:08,321 --> 00:43:11,601
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

694
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:19,691
(is probably different.)

695
00:43:20,691 --> 00:43:22,441
♪If the sky♪

696
00:43:22,951 --> 00:43:24,351
♪And the sea♪

697
00:43:24,891 --> 00:43:26,601
♪Turned upside down♪

698
00:43:28,161 --> 00:43:30,091
♪If a swimming fish♪

699
00:43:30,491 --> 00:43:33,881
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

700
00:43:35,651 --> 00:43:37,621
♪If back then♪

701
00:43:37,981 --> 00:43:42,391
♪We had never let go♪

702
00:43:42,991 --> 00:43:49,271
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

703
00:43:50,391 --> 00:43:52,541
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

704
00:43:52,541 --> 00:43:54,411
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

705
00:43:54,591 --> 00:43:57,031
♪And found our way back whole♪

706
00:43:57,871 --> 00:44:00,041
♪So let this surging love♪

707
00:44:00,041 --> 00:44:04,471
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

708
00:44:05,371 --> 00:44:07,551
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

709
00:44:07,551 --> 00:44:08,641
♪That's alright♪

710
00:44:09,181 --> 00:44:09,931
♪If we're buried♪

711
00:44:09,931 --> 00:44:12,631
♪By passing years all the better♪

712
00:44:12,891 --> 00:44:15,071
♪At least we still can keep♪

713
00:44:15,251 --> 00:44:19,671
♪This one eternal photograph♪

714
00:44:35,431 --> 00:44:37,721
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

715
00:44:37,721 --> 00:44:39,481
♪Running in opposite ways♪

716
00:44:39,601 --> 00:44:42,071
♪Searching all along the way♪

717
00:44:42,871 --> 00:44:45,031
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

718
00:44:45,221 --> 00:44:50,131
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

719
00:44:50,131 --> 00:44:53,651
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

720
00:44:53,891 --> 00:44:54,861
♪Only after loss♪

721
00:44:54,861 --> 00:44:57,491
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

722
00:44:57,901 --> 00:45:00,261
♪In another time and space♪

723
00:45:00,261 --> 00:45:01,821
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

724
00:45:01,821 --> 00:45:04,651
♪Till we grow old♪

725
00:45:05,611 --> 00:45:07,901
♪But still the sky will never♪

726
00:45:07,901 --> 00:45:10,571
♪Turn with the sea♪

727
00:45:13,091 --> 00:45:15,501
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

728
00:45:15,501 --> 00:45:20,711
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪
